AsyncOperationLog.name: AsyncOperationLog
AsyncOperationLog.description: Represents an async operations log containing progress and status information about external synchronizations to the Omnichannel Inventory service.

AsyncOperationNumber.description: The auto-generated number assigned to the operation.

Error.description: The error message for the operation. Applies only if the operation has an error.

ExternalReference.description: The unique external reference ID per type.

FinishedAt.description: The date and time the operation finished.

LastStatusUpdateAt.description: The date and time the status of the operation was last updated.

RelatedRecordId.description: The related record ID for the async request. This field is available in API version 60.0 and later.

Request.description: The request sent to the external service.

Response.description: The full response from the external service.

StartedAt.description: The date and time the operation started.

Type.description: The type of operation that is being tracked.

AsyncOperationLog.accessRules: This object is only available in Omnichannel Inventory orgs.
